   and this is the only bar.

32:07.059 --> 32:10.661
That's a good point.
    Yes. I will, um, I will
         see you soon.

32:11.463 --> 32:13.263
I'm just gonna...

32:17.236 --> 32:19.336
All right, I'll think about you.

32:19.471 --> 32:22.439
Oh, I'm sorry.
  We're closed. We're closed.

32:25.244 --> 32:26.510
[Hawkes] Bye Lana!

32:30.649 --> 32:34.384
So, what does a man worth
 50 million dollars feel like?

32:34.386 --> 32:35.986
[Angela]
        Amazing, right?

32:35.988 --> 32:37.587
I bet he's hard as a rock.

32:37.589 --> 32:38.488
Hey!

32:38.490 --> 32:40.724
What? I meant his muscles.

32:40.726 --> 32:42.326
Anyway...

32:42.328 --> 32:43.660
Try no million.

32:43.662 --> 32:46.129
I read he lost all of his
          endorsements

32:46.131 --> 32:48.332
and his team is about
          to sue him.

32:48.334 --> 32:53.503
Girls, I made him drinks and I
talked to him because I had to,
         but that's it.

32:53.505 --> 32:55.138
'Cause that's you, Lana.

32:55.140 --> 33:00.410
Sensible, like a pair
      of nurse's sneakers.

33:01.413 --> 33:05.015
What am I even worried about?

33:05.017 --> 33:09.686
We all know that men like Ryan
  don't go for women like you.

33:12.257 --> 33:14.191
Don't listen to her.

33:14.193 --> 33:15.993
No, she's right.

33:15.995 --> 33:17.728
Girl...

33:17.729 --> 33:19.462
You are either blind or you
    seriously underestimate
           yourself.

33:19.465 --> 33:20.497
You're gorgeous.

33:21.233 --> 33:22.332
Thank you.

34:28.333 --> 34:30.600
Hey, it's my, um,

34:30.601 --> 34:34.304
it's my lifeguard!
   Come to save me. Too late.

34:35.407 --> 34:38.375
I really think you shouldn't
   drink anymore, Mr. Hawkes.

34:44.416 --> 34:46.683
Fine. Screw it.

35:32.264 --> 35:33.697
Thank you.

35:49.181 --> 35:51.715
Grandma said you were
          out earlier.

35:51.717 --> 35:52.749
Were you playing soccer?

35:52.751 --> 35:55.852
No. I play with Alina.

35:56.722 --> 35:57.787
Alina?

35:57.789 --> 35:59.489
[Lana]
          <i> Who's Alina?</i>

35:59.491 --> 36:00.590
Just a girl.

36:01.693 --> 36:04.261
You never used to like
         girls before.

36:04.563 --> 36:05.896
<i> That was before.</i>

36:07.199 --> 36:08.798
Before you grow up?

36:09.635 --> 36:11.168
Goodnight, mama.

36:18.777 --> 36:20.944
Sorry about before. Uh,

36:20.946 --> 36:23.313
painkillers and daiquiris
     are a terrible combo.

36:23.315 --> 36:24.548
That's all right.

36:24.550 --> 36:26.449
That and most women,
       when they meet me,

36:26.451 --> 36:31.755
are just a lot flirtier
   than that, no, like nicer.
No, um, different...

36:31.757 --> 36:33.690
[Hawkes]
         To... to you.

36:33.692 --> 36:38.395
Oh, I'm not most women.
  And I'm definitely not your
         kind of woman.

36:38.397 --> 36:41.231
Well, I don't know if
         I'd say that.

36:43.435 --> 36:45.402
Yeah. All right.

36:45.404 --> 36:47.470
Good save, Ryan.
            Smooth.

36:51.476 --> 36:52.642
Oh, hey!

36:52.644 --> 36:54.461
Wanna take a break with me?

36:54.462 --> 36:56.279
You need to stop following me.
      I'll get in trouble.

36:56.281 --> 36:58.848
I am not following you.
           [chuckles]

37:00.786 --> 37:03.787
Oh my  ,
      I am following you.

37:03.789 --> 37:06.423
[Hawkes] All right, come on.
  I don't want you to get the
wrong idea here.

37:07.759 --> 37:09.593
Mr. Zimmer

37:09.595 --> 37:12.229
Good evening, Mr. Hawkes.

37:12.598 --> 37:15.398
Ms. Kalinina, a word, please.

37:24.810 --> 37:26.977
This is unacceptable.

37:26.979 --> 37:29.213
Uh, excuse me. Um,

37:29.214 --> 37:31.448
she was actually helping me
 decide which drink I ordered.

37:31.450 --> 37:32.782
What was the one you
        suggested again?

37:32.784 --> 37:35.318
A dirty martini,
          upside down.

37:35.320 --> 37:37.087
That's the thing.

37:37.088 --> 37:38.855
See, I forgot the upside down
 part. Can I get one of those?

37:38.857 --> 37:39.789
Certainly, sir.

37:39.791 --> 37:42.626
You have to take Friday off.

37:42.628 --> 37:45.229
Did I do anything wrong?

37:45.230 --> 37:47.831
You cannot work four weeks
without a day off.

37:48.567 --> 37:50.300
And goodnight to you, sir.

37:51.637 --> 37:52.736
Goodnight

37:53.805 --> 37:54.904
Thanks.

37:56.475 --> 37:59.409
Now, where is my martini?

38:02.481 --> 38:04.598
[Hawkes] Okay, new idea.
      Hear me out on this.

38:04.599 --> 38:06.716
What if we meet up off
   the boat? You're free now,

38:06.718 --> 38:09.352
so are there rules against
   meeting up on the island?

38:09.354 --> 38:11.488
[Lana] No, but that's not
        going to happen.

38:11.490 --> 38:13.823
Why not? Look, I mean,
     I'm telling you, Lana,

38:13.825 --> 38:17.060
I am a great tour guide.
    I can Google pretty much
   anything you need to know.

38:17.062 --> 38:19.863
And you? You, you can
teach me Russian.

38:19.865 --> 38:21.998
You want to learn Russian?

38:22.000 --> 38:24.901
Yeah. I hear they have a very
    cheery outlook on life.

38:24.903 --> 38:25.869
[Lana laughs]

38:26.571 --> 38:27.971
Good night, Ryan.

38:27.973 --> 38:29.372
Wait, was that a yes?

38:29.374 --> 38:31.841
Okay, yes, but now be quiet,
            please!

38:31.843 --> 38:33.810
Whoa! Did you hear that?
         She said yes!

38:33.812 --> 38:35.612
She said yes, everybody!

38:38.850 --> 38:41.735
Hey, Ms. Kalinina,

38:41.736 --> 38:44.621
the ship leaves tomorrow at 10
  o'clock so be on the boat no
      later then midnight.

38:44.623 --> 38:45.922
Thank you.

39:06.878 --> 39:07.711
[Lana] Hello

39:07.713 --> 39:08.678
[shopkeeper] Hello.

39:09.348 --> 39:10.747
[Lana]
     What do you have here?

39:10.749 --> 39:11.848
[shopkeeper]
        Oh, everything.

39:13.719 --> 39:17.787
I like this one.
        It's beautiful.

39:21.126 --> 39:22.959
[Lana] No, this would be
       perfect actually.

39:22.961 --> 39:25.895
[shopkeeper] Please go ahead.
           Thank you.

39:25.897 --> 39:27.314
Thanks a lot.

39:27.315 --> 39:28.732
Good morning there,
      my sweet surrender.

39:28.734 --> 39:29.766
Hi...

39:29.768 --> 39:32.769
Oh, relax. It'll be our
         little secret.

39:32.771 --> 39:34.671
You're gonna follow me all day,
          aren't you?

39:34.673 --> 39:36.873
Well, now that you mention it...

39:38.410 --> 39:41.745
[Lana] So, I was thinking about
   all those sorrows you say

39:41.747 --> 39:43.146
you like to drown yourself from.

39:43.148 --> 39:44.748
[Hawkes] We're not gonna talk
    about that now, are we?

39:44.750 --> 39:47.817
Well, I'm Russian.
    We don't do small talk.

39:47.819 --> 39:51.521
All right. You like the
    heavy stuff. Fine, okay.

39:51.523 --> 39:54.891
Well, after not making peace
 with the fact that my knee is

39:54.893 --> 40:00.630
shot and my endorsements have
 de-endorsed me and if I do get
         to play again,

40:00.632 --> 40:02.932
I won't be the player
          I once was.

40:02.934 --> 40:06.035
I guess what's there to
    worry about? My life is
        basically over.

40:08.607 --> 40:13.143
Ryan, but I believe when
 one door closes, others open.

40:13.145 --> 40:16.613
Just don't stare at the
    closed one for too long.

40:21.686 --> 40:23.453
You sure you're not some kind
   of undercover journalist?

40:23.455 --> 40:25.422
You're way too wise to be
       working on a boat.

40:29.461 --> 40:33.062
Anyway, it's uh, it's not
   really about seeing doors,

40:33.064 --> 40:36.032
it's honestly, it's about
       how people see me.

40:37.536 --> 40:41.171
Are you afraid that people
   are not gonna like you for
          who you are?

40:41.173 --> 40:44.541
Hell no. I know they won't.

40:44.976 --> 40:47.477
When you're in the spotlight,
   everybody wants to be your
            friend.

40:47.479 --> 40:49.646
But as I'm finding out,

40:49.648 --> 40:52.782
when that goes away,
[whistles] goes everybody else.

40:54.719 --> 40:57.620
But now that you have time
     to do something else,

40:57.622 --> 40:59.722
you might make some
         real friends.

41:01.460 --> 41:04.594
If I'm, uh, perfectly honest,

41:04.596 --> 41:08.164
it's the something else that
    I'm most worried about.

41:11.136 --> 41:13.102
I don't know anything else.

41:16.508 --> 41:20.109
Lana, I wasn't always such
     an asshole, you know.

41:21.012 --> 41:25.582
I trained my whole life
    to be the best I can be,
         at one thing.

41:25.584 --> 41:28.685
All this other stuff kind of
 just came with the territory,
I guess.

41:31.857 --> 41:34.123
It was a way...

41:34.960 --> 41:37.594
Lana, without soccer...

41:39.664 --> 41:40.730
I'm not really anything.

41:40.732 --> 41:44.534
I'm sure you have many
         more talents.

41:44.536 --> 41:47.637
There's a whole world out there
   waiting to be discovered.

41:48.640 --> 41:53.743
But to [indiscernible]
  you discover nothing without
     taking the first step.

41:59.851 --> 42:02.952
Hey! Hey! Oh, that's it.
    Now you're gonna get it!

42:03.722 --> 42:05.822
[Lana laughs]

42:09.060 --> 42:12.161
[yelling and laughing]

42:34.886 --> 42:36.319
[Lana] Let's check it out.

42:37.722 --> 42:38.922
[Hawkes] Hello, sir.

42:38.924 --> 42:40.023
[Lana] Hi.

42:40.025 --> 42:42.559
Who are you, like the
        local locksmith?

42:44.796 --> 42:47.597
Uh-huh...
           I'm not...

42:47.599 --> 42:49.699
[Hawkes] Oh, I... okay.

42:50.335 --> 42:54.337
Ah, I get it.
     The lock is the heart.

42:54.339 --> 42:56.839
You give it to someone, then...

42:56.841 --> 42:59.642
Throw away the key,
   making the lock permanent?

43:00.111 --> 43:02.111
That's beautiful.

43:02.113 --> 43:04.581
[Lana] It's very nice.

43:04.583 --> 43:07.951
-Oh, no, no. No, no thank you.
          -Oh. No, no.

43:07.953 --> 43:10.053
-[Lana] Thank you, sir.
  -[Hawkes] I think you might
      have the wrong idea.

43:11.756 --> 43:13.356
Thank you, thank you.

43:21.066 --> 43:24.167
Hey, kid, your ball.

43:25.737 --> 43:27.136
Your ball, kid.

43:27.138 --> 43:29.372
You are...
          Ryan Hawkes?

43:29.374 --> 43:31.007
Yes. Nice to meet you.

43:31.009 --> 43:32.742
Guys! It's Ryan Hawkes!

43:32.744 --> 43:34.110
I think we should probably go.

43:34.112 --> 43:36.679
No, no, no.
    You're going over there.

43:36.681 --> 43:38.881
Ryan, it's gonna make their
             year.

43:38.883 --> 43:41.684
Yeah, I don't know about that.
            Hey hey!

43:41.987 --> 43:43.219
[kid]
    Come play with us, man!

43:43.221 --> 43:45.688
Shut up, stupid.
     He can't play no more.

43:45.824 --> 43:47.824
Hey, I can play.

43:47.826 --> 43:50.693
Not full speed,
  but enough to teach you kids
        a thing or two.

43:50.695 --> 43:51.661
